Utterance: Hi there! It’s nice to see you again. How have you been since our last session?
I’ve been doing okay, a bit better actually. I tried that mindfulness exercise.
That’s great to hear! How did it go for you?
It helped me relax a bit, especially before bed. I think I slept a little better.
Wonderful! Consistency can make a big difference. Have you been able to integrate it into your routine?
Yes, I try to do it most nights now.
That’s excellent progress! You also mentioned looking into community events. Were you able to find any?
I did! I found a local art class I’m thinking about attending.
That sounds exciting! How do you feel about participating in that?
I’m nervous but also kind of excited. I haven’t done anything like that in a long time.
It’s completely normal to feel nervous. What do you think might help ease that anxiety?
Maybe just reminding myself that it’s okay to be a beginner.
Absolutely! Everyone starts somewhere. Focusing on enjoying the process rather than the outcome can also help.
Yeah, I’ll try to keep that in mind.
Great! How about your insurance studies? How has that been going?
I’ve been breaking it down into smaller sections like we talked about, and it’s been helpful.
Fantastic! Have you noticed any improvements in your understanding or retention of the material?
Yes, I feel more confident with the information now.
That’s wonderful to hear! Celebrating those small victories is important. Are there any particular topics that you find challenging?
Some of the regulations are a bit confusing.
Would it help to seek out additional resources or study groups for those topics?
That could be useful. I’ll look into it.
Excellent! It’s great that you’re being proactive about your learning. How have you been feeling emotionally lately?
I’ve had some ups and downs, but overall, I feel more motivated.
That’s a positive shift! What do you think has contributed to that motivation?
I think it’s just having some goals to work towards and feeling like I’m making progress.
That’s a powerful realization. Setting and achieving goals can really boost our mood. Have you thought about any new goals you’d like to set?
I’d like to finish my insurance courses by the end of the month.
That’s a great goal! What steps will you take to ensure you meet that deadline?
I’ll schedule dedicated study time each day and stick to it.
Sounds like a solid plan! Remember to be flexible with yourself, too. Life can sometimes throw unexpected challenges our way.
True, I’ll keep that in mind.
Is there anything else you’d like to discuss today?
I’ve been thinking about my mom a lot lately.
I’m glad you brought that up. What thoughts or feelings have come up for you?
I just miss her and think about how much she supported me.
It’s completely natural to miss loved ones, especially during moments of reflection. How do you usually cope with those feelings?
I try to remember the good times and talk to her in my head.
That’s a lovely way to honor her memory. Have you considered writing down your thoughts or memories about her?
I haven’t, but that sounds like a good idea.
Writing can be a therapeutic way to process your feelings. Would you like to set a goal to write about her this week?
Yes, I’d like that.
Great! I look forward to hearing about your experience next time. Remember, it’s okay to feel what you’re feeling.
Thank you, I appreciate that.
You’re welcome! Take care of yourself, and I’ll see you soon.
Bye!
